-- Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, Pomalca, Relapasa, Siderperu
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-23T17:33:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/peru-stocks-casa-grande-pomalca-relapasa-siderperu.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of 12:19 p.m. in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 1.6 percent to 20,396.27. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 1.9 percent to 2,624.39.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA known as Siderperu, fell 4 percent to 71 centimos on
investor concern that the Greek debt crisis may cut European
demand for Peruvian exports, said Estefany Castillo, an analyst
at Scotiabank Peru.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, dropped 3.5 percent to 82 centimos after crude declined
in  New York .  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, slid 2 percent to $1.  Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar
producer, fell 3.4 percent to 57 centimos after sugar slumped
for a fourth session in New York.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peruâ€™s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, dropped 2 percent to 14.70 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
